news.title: Government has taken lot of steps to clean realty sector: Housing secretary
news.para: Manoj Joshi said the stamp duty in property transactions has come down and it should further reduce as this plays an important role in determining whether businesses are done in a fair manner or using black money.

news.title: Gurugram administration reconstitutes probe panel on Chintel Paradiso tower
news.para: It will have as members the chief engineer (building), PWD B&R; superintending engineer, Gurugram circle (PWD B&R); district town planner, enforcement; and Rajecv Kumar, ACP Udyog Vihar.

news.title: Telangana government to auction over 2,000 flats to realtors
news.para: The Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) will conduct auctions on March 24 and is hoping to get about Rs 1,000 crore.

news.title: Panel to resettle 100 more Chintels Paradiso families, has three months to file report
news.para: The families are apprehensive about the structural safety of their buildings and want to move out. They will be shifted to other flats within the society by the developer, officials said.

news.title: ATS Tourmaline residents concerned over water leakage in basement for eight months
news.para: Spread across 10 acres, the project was launched in 2013. Possession of flats started in 2019. Out of 410 flats, around 75 families are currently living in the five towers of the residential complex.

news.title: Haryana forms panel to examine structural strength of buildings
news.para: Kaushal made the statement days after the sequential collapse of drawing-room roofs of a flat from the sixth floor to the first floor in a highrise in the city, in which two women residents of the building were killed and a senior central government officer was critically injured.

news.title: Two more China Evergrande property assets taken over by state-owned firms
news.para: The world's most indebted property developer on Jan. 26 transferred its control over a theme park called Evergrande Fairyland in the Nansha district of Guangzhou to Minmetals International Trust Co, according to the records.

news.title: Saint-Gobain looks to build on construction momentum after record year
news.para: The French construction materials group, which posted an 18.4% rise year-on-year in organic revenue growth for 2021, said it had increased prices in an attempt to offset the impact of inflation.

news.title: Kolkata: More ready homes to be at your disposal this year than last two years
news.para: While Kolkata used to see 15,000-17,000 ready units hit the market each year, the last two years saw a decline in finished homes arriving in the market.

news.title: Land acquisition survey for Kochi GIFT City completed
news.para: T Devarajan, special tahsildar appointed for the land acquisition of the project, said that the field survey was completed on Thursday and the documentation procedures regarding this would be completed within some days.

news.title: Greater Noida's first construction and demolition waste plant by next year?
news.para: So far, over 2,000 tonnes of debris have been lifted from more than 35 locations of the city and transported to the site in Ecotech III.

news.title: Raze illegal buildings on nalas in Manikonda and Puppalguda: NGT
news.para: With unauthorised buildings blocking water bodies in these areas, the NGT asked the Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) and chief secretary Somesh Kumar to pull down all identified illegal structures.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body plans to widen its house tax ambit, eyes Rs 80 crore more revenue
news.para: “A GIS survey is in the final stage. We have studied 97 of the 100 wards here. Simultaneously, the corporation is carrying out a door-to-door survey and the data is being collated,” said Sanjeev Sinha, the chief tax assessment officer.

news.title: Delhi: Why legal tag has failed to enthuse home owners
news.para: The process of registration of properties began on December 16, 2019 and 20 residents of two unauthorised colonies, Raja Vihar and Suraj Park, in north Delhi were the first to receive conveyance deeds and registration papers of their properties on January 3, 2020.

news.title: Nashik civic body adds 36,000 new properties under tax net
news.para: With this, the number of total properties under the tax ambit across Nashik city has increased to 4.96 lakh properties. Of these, 15,000 new properties have been brought under tax net in the last three months (November to January).
